(intIssueWidth, DCacheMiss).explanation: Integer issue width determines how many integer instructions can be dispatched per cycle, and higher issue widths generate more memory access requests that can lead to increased data cache misses;

(intIssueWidth, enablePrefetching).explanation: Integer issue width is a hardware dispatch parameter while prefetching is a memory optimization technique - they operate independently in different processor subsystems;

(intIssueWidth, nDCacheMSHRs).explanation: Issue width affects instruction dispatch rate while MSHR count is a cache design parameter for handling outstanding misses - no direct causal relationship exists;
